                        <locus from="1" to="160">ff. 1-160</locus>
                        <note>
                           <p>Collection of transcripts for 14 treaties, agreements, supplements, and addenda between the British East India Company's Madras Presidency and the rulers of Hyderabad, Arcot, and Travancore. However, the majority of the contents involve Tipu Sultan, the division and distribution of his territory (Mysore), and the instalation of Krishna Rajah as ruler. Treaties range in date, 26 February 1768 to 12 January 1805, each copy attested by C P Prouly (or Rowth?), Persian Translator to Government </p>
                           <p>Watermarked paper: 1) W. Tucker 1839; 2) Britannia in oval with crown </p>
                           <p>Foliation in Persian </p>
                        </note>
